\f0\b\fs56 \cf2 UI Context MCP\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\i\b0\fs26 \cf3 A developer tool for AI-powered live UI debugging\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\i0\b\fs36 \cf2 Problem\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 Developers debugging local web apps constantly need to connect three things mentally: what they see in the browser, the underlying DOM and CSS, and the source code and runtime conditions behind it.\
Today this is fragmented across browser DevTools, the IDE, and AI assistants. Even with Claude Code, Cursor, or Copilot, there is no seamless way to attach an AI query directly to a live UI element. Developers are forced to copy HTML into chat, describe the UI in words, or inspect the DOM step-by-step manually.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Core Gap\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 There is no system that allows:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa200\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\i \cf4 "Select a UI element in a running local web app \uc0\u8594  ask an AI question \u8594  get reasoning grounded in actual DOM + state context."\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\i0\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Proposed Solution\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 A local-first "UI Context MCP" system that connects live browser UI selection with Claude Code. The developer selects any element in a localhost app, and Claude receives structured, layered context \'97 from raw DOM all the way up to source file and line number.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 Architecture\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs18 \cf5 [Browser \'97 localhost app]\
        \uc0\u8595   element selection / Ctrl+Shift+K\
[Chrome Extension \'97 content script]\
        \uc0\u8595   layered context capture (all 4 layers)\
[Local Bridge Server \'97 Node.js]\
        \uc0\u8595   structured UI_CONTEXT payload\
[MCP Server \'97 UI Context Tools]\
        \uc0\u8595   analyze_ui_element(question, UI_CONTEXT)\
[Claude Code]\
        \uc0\u8595 \
[Explanation + Debug + Suggested Fix]\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf2 Layered Context System\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 Context is captured in four independent layers. Each layer is attempted in order. If a layer is unavailable, it is skipped and Claude is told explicitly what is missing. The tool is useful in every environment, not just ideal ones.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

