\f3\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 Layer 2 \'97 Accessibility Tree\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 Always available. The browser builds this automatically from your HTML. Stable (roles don't change when class names do) and captures intent \'97 what the element is supposed to do, not just what it looks like.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs18 \cf5 accessibility: \{\
  role:      'button',\
  name:      'Checkout',\
  disabled:  true,\
  ariaHidden: false,\
\}\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf4 Layer 3 \'97 React Fiber (Component Mapping)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 Available when React is running in the browser. React stamps every DOM node with a hidden reference to its internal Fiber node at runtime via a property like __reactFiber$abc123. Walking .return (parent) up the fiber tree gives the full component hierarchy.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

