\f0\b \cf8 Hook State Reading\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa120\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs22 \cf0 useState values are stored as a linked list in fiber.memoizedState. React 18 also exposes _debugHookTypes which names the hook type for each slot. Together they give partial named state:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li720\sa40\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs18 \cf5 // fiber._debugHookTypes = ['useState', 'useState']\
// fiber.memoizedState linked list:\
//   node1.memoizedState = 0       (count)\
//   node2.memoizedState = 'hello' (name)\
\
hooks: [\
  \{ type: 'useState', value: 0 \},\
  \{ type: 'useState', value: 'hello' \}\
]\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f3\fs24 \cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs22 \cf0 Limitation: 
\f2\b0 Variable names (count, name) are stripped at runtime. _debugHookTypes gives the hook type per slot but not the developer's variable name. Full named state requires the React DevTools hook \'97 a future enhancement.\
\pard\pardeftab720\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

